--[[ LNP:NewColor(r,g,b) Create Color variable from R=red, G=green, and B=blue parameters. Parameter accept range from 0 to 255
LNP:DeviceCount() Get total count of detected Lighting Node Pro device
LNP:GetDeviceName(index) Get LNP device name, device parameter index start from 0
LNP:GetDeviceSerial(index) Get LNP device serial number, device parameter index starts from 0
LNP:GetDeviceVersion(index) Get LNP device version, device parameter index starts from 0
LNP:SetColor(index,channel,color) Set LNP LED colors, index = device index, channel = channel index, color = colors array
LNP:SetColor(sernum,channel,color) Set LNP LED colors, sernum= device serial number, channel = channel index, color = colors array ]]
--example script --fill white color from LED 1 to 16 import ("System.Threading") color = {} local i=1 while i<=16 do color[i] = LNP:NewColor(255,255,255) LNP:SetColor(0,0,color) i = i + 1 Thread.Sleep(100) end
